07/02/2008
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A Turkish cargo ship burst into flames in the Adriatic Sea near Croatian shores early on Wednesday (February 6th) threatening an ecological disaster in the area. 
The ship, carrying nine tonnes of "hazardous" materials and 200 trucks, was sailing from Istanbul to the port of Trieste, Italy. 
Three ships sailing near the scene of the accident were immediately sent to help and managed to save all 22 crew members and nine passengers onboard. 
(Index.hr, Vecernji List, Javno.com, B92, Anadolu news agency - 06/02/08)
